values:
I rarely ever update, and I think I'm going to start doing it more often. I'm&nbsp; always upset when my friends don't update enough since I barely ever get to see them, so I figured I should update more often, too.
So, here's what's been up with me.&nbsp;
I started my new job at the Reiman Gardens Gift Shop last week. I like working there a lot so far. The latest it's open is 4:30, so that gives me all of my nights for hanging out with Sam and doing homework. It's pretty slow right now so I'm not getting to work that often, but I don't mind.
Classes started last week. They're all going okay so far. We'll see how they all end up. I'm the only girl in a few of my classes and it's really strange. I also have the same lab teacher I had last year that I really don't like. I'm trying to deal with it, though.
I took Mr. Kitty-butts into the vet on Monday. He had some type of worms, poor baby! But he's okay now. He's currently laying behind my computer, probably getting ready to take a nice nap.&nbsp;
Hopefully I'll be able to make it back down to Illinois soon. When I come down next, I think I'll stay in Pekin for a night, then go down to Bloomington. Maybe I'll be able to go down in February sometime.&nbsp;

Well, that's really about it. Nothing much has been going on here. Except that the cat just sneezed on the back of my computer. SICK!

-Stephanie

Grades already posted after my first final today.&nbsp;
A in Geology 100!

Not like I was expecting anything else...
&nbsp;
Now I just have to take my hard one for today.

-Stephanie
